        <p><hi rend="bold">Richard Bloch (Hupka),</hi>  brother of <ref cRef="kaposy_frau">Mrs. Kaposy</ref> and <ref cRef="hupka_felix">Felix Hupka</ref>.  In 1918, Bloch had Zionist literature sent to Schenker.  He was evidently a supporter of Zionism, and perhaps changed his family name from Hupka to Bloch for idealistic reasons.</p>
